": "1907-11-08", "dates": ["1907-11-08"], "description": ["page two FRIDAY NOVEMBER 8 1907 SANTA FE NEW MEXICAN THE NEW MEXICAN PRINTING COMPANY PUBLISHERS VIAX FROST Editor JOHN K STAUFFER SecyTreas EDWIN F COARD City Editor Entered as Second Class Matter at the Santa Fe Postofflce RATES OF SUBSCRIPTION Dally per week by carrier 20 Dally per month by carrier 75 Oaily per month by mall 65 tally per year by mall 700 Dally six months by mail 375 Weekly per year 200 Weekly six months 100 Weekly per quarter 75 OFFICIAL PAPER OF SANTA FE COUNTY The New Mexican is the oldest n ewspaper In New Mexico It Is sent to every postofflce in the Territory an d has a large and growing circulation among the intelligent and progresslv e people of the Southwest UMION CURRENCY REFORM LAWS NEC ESSARY Under the heading A Better Cur rency System Needed the Pueblo Chieftain discusses the needs of the country in that respect very sensibly and very timely and expresses the views and opinions of the solid and steady people especially of tliose mod erately well to do who work for a living and for a competency and who are in the great majority in the coun try The"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2020-09-15T13:27:17.261Z", "group": ["ndnp/nmu", "university-of-new-mexico-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84020630/1907-11-08/ed-1/?sp=2", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:nmu:batch_nmu_huxley_ver01:data:sn84020630:00416150266:1907110801:0912/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=465&w=299", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:nmu:batch_nmu_huxley_ver01:data:sn84020630:00416150266:1907110801:0912/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=930&w=599", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/nmu/batch_nmu_huxley_ver01/data/sn84020630/00416150266/1907110801/0912.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 2, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "new mexico", "santa fe county"